# Course Title :	MACHINE LEARNING FOR CYBER SECURITY
1.		Perform a time series decomposition of a dataset with seasonal and trend components. 
2.		Using historical network traffic data, apply time series forecasting methods (like ARIMA or Prophet) to predict potential DDoS attacks. 	
3.		Implement an ensemble learning method (e.g., Random Forest or Gradient Boosting) to classify cyber-attacks. 
4.		Build a logistic regression model to classify URLs as either legitimate or malicious. 
5.		Apply a Support Vector Machine (SVM) to classify URLs into legitimate and malicious categories 
6.		Using a set of URLs, detect abnormal patterns using feature engineering. 
7.		Build a machine learning model to solve CAPTCHA challenges. 
8.		Using an email dataset, detect patterns of email spoofing. 
9.		Implement a text classification algorithm (e.g., Naive Bayes or SVM) to classify emails as spam or not spam. 
10.		Use k-means to classify network events into normal and abnormal categories
11.		Develop a decision tree classifier to detect malicious data injections within databases.
12.		Develop a model that uses context (e.g., timestamp, source IP, and event type) to detect malicious events within wireless sensor networks. 
